## 3. Task Management (Plans.md)

### Marker Reference

| Marker | Meaning | Set By |
|--------|---------|--------|
| `pm:requested` | Requested by PM (compat: cursor:requested) | PM (Cursor/PM Claude) |
| `cc:TODO` | Claude Code not started | Either |
| `cc:WIP` | Claude Code in progress | Claude Code |
| `cc:done` | Claude Code completed | Claude Code |
| `pm:confirmed` | PM review completed (compat: cursor:confirmed) | PM (Cursor/PM Claude) |
| `cursor:requested` | (compat) Same as pm:requested | Cursor |
| `cursor:confirmed` | (compat) Same as pm:confirmed | Cursor |
| `blocked` | Blocked | Either |

### State Transitions

```
pm:requested -> cc:WIP -> cc:done -> pm:confirmed
```

---

## 4. CI/CD Rules

### Claude Code Scope

- CI error auto-fix (up to 3 attempts)
- Deployment to staging environment
- Production deployment is prohibited (Cursor's responsibility)

### 3-Strike Rule

When CI fails 3 consecutive times:
1. Stop auto-fix attempts
2. Create an escalation report
3. Defer judgment to Cursor

---

## 5. Commit Message Convention

```
feat: new feature
fix: bug fix
docs: documentation
refactor: refactoring
test: tests
chore: miscellaneous
```

Example: `feat: add user authentication`

---

## 6. Prohibited Actions

### Claude Code Restrictions

- Production environment direct deployment
- More than 3 CI auto-fix attempts
- Work outside scope (e.g., adding unrequested features)
- Security-related setting changes (API keys, authentication, etc.)

### Shared Restrictions

- force push (`--force` / `--force-with-lease`)
- Committing sensitive information

> **Note**: For solo development projects, direct push to main is acceptable. CI runs validation on push to main, so the quality gate is maintained. Switch to mandatory PRs if collaborators are added.

---

## 7. Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

| Symptom | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| CI keeps failing | Attempt 3 times, then escalate to Cursor |
| Task is unclear | Ask Cursor for clarification |
| Plans.md is outdated | Check status with `/sync-status` |

